amesmarket.filereaders

Class LoadCaseScenarioReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • amesmarket.filereaders.AbstractConfigFileReader<LoadProfileCollection>
      • amesmarket.filereaders.LoadCaseScenarioReader

  • public class LoadCaseScenarioReader
extends AbstractConfigFileReader<LoadProfileCollection>
    Read in a data file representing a single LoadProfile scenario. The reader fails fast. As soon as any problem is encountered in the data file format, an excpetion is thrown. TODO: Describe the expected file format, once it solidifies.

      • read

        protected LoadProfileCollection read()
                              throws BadDataFileFormatException
        Read in load profiles until the end of the file/reader stream. The LoadControl object must be set before calling this method. The return object has not been checked for consistency. The client is responsible for checking the object when it is appropriate to do so! Before calling this method (or any of the other read methods) the expected scenario number must be set with setExpectedScenarioNumber(int). The value of the expected scenario will be used to validate the scenario data at the end of the method. Breaks the general protocol for AbstractConfigFileReader.move(boolean). This is because of the loop and-a-half issue, coupled with needing to look ahead in the stream to check for the end of loop and no push-back into the input stream.
        Specified by:
        read in class AbstractConfigFileReader<LoadProfileCollection>
        Parameters:
        expectedEntries - expected number of entries in each line of the data stream.
        Returns:
        a list of load profiles.
        Throws:
